  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A circle has a radius of <math alttext=\"2.1\"><mn>2.1</mn>\n</math> inches. The area of the circle is <math alttext=\"b pi\"><mi>b</mi><mi>&#960;</mi></math> square inches, where <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math> is a constant. What is the value of <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "4.41",
    "441/100"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math alttext=\"4.41\"><mn>4.41</mn>\n</math>. The area, <math alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi>\n</math>, of a circle is given by the formula <math alttext=\"upper A equals pi r squared\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&pi;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where <math alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi>\n</math> is the radius of the circle. It's given that the area of the circle is&nbsp;<math alttext=\"b pi\"><mi>b</mi><mi>&pi;</mi></math> square inches, where <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math> is a constant, and the radius of the circle is <math alttext=\"2.1\"><mn>2.1</mn>\n</math> inches. Substituting <math alttext=\"b pi\"><mi>b</mi><mi>&pi;</mi></math> for <math alttext=\"upper A\"><mi>A</mi>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"2.1\"><mn>2.1</mn>\n</math> for <math alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi>\n</math> in the formula <math alttext=\"upper A equals pi r squared\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&pi;</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;yields <math alttext=\"b pi equals pi left parenthesis 2.1 squared right parenthesis\"><mi>b</mi><mi>&pi;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&pi;</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>2.1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced></math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by&nbsp;<math alttext=\"pi\"><mi>&pi;</mi></math> yields <math alttext=\"b equals 4.41\"><mrow>\n<mi>b</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>4.41</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Therefore, the value of <math alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi>\n</math> is <math alttext=\"4.41\"><mn>4.41</mn>\n</math>.</p>",
